defs.docs: Interface to random number generators in Rust.

defs.name: distributions
defs.docs: Sampling from random distributions.

defs.name: range
defs.docs: Generating numbers between two others.

defs.name: Range
defs.docs: Sample values uniformly between two bounds.

defs.name: SampleRange
defs.docs:
The helper trait for types that have a sensible way to sample
 uniformly between two values. This should not be used directly,
 and is only to facilitate `Range`.

defs.name: construct_range
defs.docs:
The helper trait for types that have a sensible way to sample
 uniformly between two values. This should not be used directly,
 and is only to facilitate `Range`.

defs.name: sample_range
defs.docs:
The helper trait for types that have a sensible way to sample
 uniformly between two values. This should not be used directly,
 and is only to facilitate `Range`.

The chi-squared distribution `χ²(k)`, where `k` is the degrees of
 freedom.

defs.docs: The Fisher F distribution `F(m, n)`.

defs.name: StudentT

The Student t distribution, `t(nu)`, where `nu` is the degrees of

defs.name: normal
defs.docs: The normal and derived distributions.

defs.docs:
A wrapper around an `f64` to generate N(0, 1) random numbers

defs.name: IndependentSample
defs.docs: `Sample`s that do not require keeping track of state.

defs.docs: `Sample`s that do not require keeping track of state.

defs.name: RandSample
defs.docs:
A wrapper for generating types that implement `Rand` via the

defs.name: reseeding
defs.docs:
A wrapper around another RNG that reseeds it after it
 generates a certain number of random bytes.

defs.name: ReseedingRng
defs.docs:
A wrapper around any RNG which reseeds the underlying RNG after it
 has generated a certain number of random bytes.

defs.name: reseeder
defs.docs: Controls the behavior when reseeding the RNG.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (rng: R, generation_threshold: usize, reseeder: Rsdr) -> ReseedingRng<R, Rsdr>

defs.name: Reseeder
defs.docs: Something that can be used to reseed an RNG via `ReseedingRng`.

defs.name: reseed
defs.docs: Something that can be used to reseed an RNG via `ReseedingRng`.

defs.name: ReseedWithDefault
defs.docs:
Reseed an RNG using a `Default` instance. This reseeds by
 replacing the RNG with the result of a `Default::default` call.

defs.docs:
A wrapper for generating floating point numbers uniformly in the
